We could be wrong, but this one looks like it might be an issue with
missing quotes. Always quote template expression brackets when they
start a value. For instance:

    with_items:

2020-08-09 07:32:54,716 p=46612 u=root |  ERROR! Syntax Error while loading YAML.
  did not find expected key

The error appears to be in '/etc/ansible/roles/iDrac/tasks/rac_playbooks/ESXi_configuration/esxi_image_set_excel.yml': line 40, column 165, but may
be elsewhere in the file depending on the exact syntax problem.

The offending line appears to be:

    - name: Set ESXi6.5 Remote Image to boot from
      raw: 'racadm -r "{{ item.address }}" -u "{{ iDRAC_Username }}" -p "{{ iDRAC_Password }}" remoteimage -c -u "{{ share_user }}" -p "{{ share_pass }}" -l {% if '6.5' in item.os_image %} "{{ share_esxi6.5_path }}" {% elif '6' in item.os_image %} "{{ share_esxi6_path }}" {% endif %}'
                                                                                                                                                                    ^ here
We could be wrong, but this one looks like it might be an issue with
missing quotes. Always quote template expression brackets when they
start a value. For instance:

    with_items:
      - {{ foo }}

Should be written as:

    with_items:
      - "{{ foo }}"
